==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: neb'jə-lə
*[[IPA]]: /ˈnebjələ/
*[[SAMPA]]: /<tt>"nebj@l@</tt>/

===Etymology===
French ''[[nubis]]'', "cloud", Latin ''[[nebula]]'', "little cloud", "mist". Akin to Greek ''[[νεφέλη]]'', "cloud", German ''[[Nebel]]'', "mist", "nebula", Old Norse ''[[nifl]]''.

===Noun===
'''nebula''' (plural: '''nebulae''')

#{{astronomy}} A [[cloud]] in [[outer space]] consisting of [[gas]] or [[dust]] (e.g. a cloud formed after a [[star]] [[explode]]s).

